# Frontend Rules

## Style

- TypeScript strict mode. No `any` — use `unknown` + type guards if needed.
- Format with `prettier`. Lint with `eslint`.
- Use TailwindCSS for styling. No CSS modules, no styled-components.

## Components

- Functional components only. Use named exports.
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks (`hooks/use-*.ts`).
- Keep components under 150 lines. Split into sub-components if larger.
- Colocate component-specific types in the same file.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — inline fetch, no separation
export function Dashboard() {
  const [data, setData] = useState(null);
  useEffect(() => { fetch("/api/...").then(...) }, []);
  return <div>...</div>;
}

// ✅ GOOD — logic in hook, component is pure UI
export function Dashboard() {
  const { positions, isLoading } = usePositions();
  if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />;
  return <PositionTable data={positions} />;
}
```

## Data Fetching

- Use `swr` or `react-query` for server state. Don't roll your own cache.
- API client goes in `lib/api.ts` — single source of truth for all endpoints.
- Type all API responses with shared interfaces from `types/`.

## File Structure

```
frontend/
  app/            # Next.js app router pages
  components/     # Reusable UI components
    ui/           # Primitives (Button, Card, etc.)
  hooks/          # Custom hooks
  lib/            # Utilities, API client
  types/          # Shared TypeScript interfaces
```
